<p>I have a View in my ASP.NET MVC application, which when it renders throws a null reference exception at the line of code that calls the <code>AntiForgeryToken()</code> method on the <code>HtmlHelper</code> class. Here is the relevant snippet of code from the view:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="form-group"&gt;     &lt;label id="lblMessage"&gt;&lt;/label&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="form-group"&gt;     @Html.LabelFor(model =&gt; model.CardNumber,              htmlAttributes: new { @class = "control-label col-md-2" })     &lt;div class="col-md-10"&gt;         @Html.EditorFor(model =&gt; model.CardNumber,                 new { htmlAttributes = new                          { @class = "form-control", id = "CardNumber" } })     &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  ... more controls to capture credit card info  @using (Html.BeginForm("AddBillingInformation",  "Business", FormMethod.Post,  new { id = "frmAddBillingInformation" })) {     @Html.AntiForgeryToken()      &lt;div class="form-horizontal"&gt;         &lt;input type="hidden" id="BusinessId" name="BusinessId" value="@Model.BusinessId" /&gt;         &lt;input type="hidden" id="StripeToken" name="BusinessId" value="@Model.StripeToken" /&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      &lt;div class="form-group"&gt;         &lt;div class="col-md-offset-2 col-md-10"&gt;             &lt;input type="submit" value="Add"               class="btn btn-default" id="btnAddBillingInformation" /&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; } </code></pre>  <p>And the exception I get:</p>  <pre><code>System.NullReferenceException: Object reference not set to an  instance of an object.  Line 43: @using (Html.BeginForm("AddBillingInformation",               "Business", FormMethod.Post,                new { id = "frmAddBillingInformation" })) Line 44: { Line 45:     @Html.AntiForgeryToken() Line 46:      Line 47:     &lt;div class="form-horizontal"&gt;  StackTrace:        at ASP._Page_Views_Business_AddBillingInformation_cshtml.Execute() in         Path\To\My\Sou